# Tailwind CSS v4 Styling Guidelines

## Core Principles
- Prefer Tailwind utility classes for styling over custom CSS.
- Keep custom CSS minimal and global-only (e.g., theme tokens, base styles) in `app/globals.css`.
- Avoid inline styles (`style={{...}}`) unless required for dynamic values that Tailwind cannot express.

## Theming & Tokens (globals.css)
- Use CSS variables as the source of truth for theme colors (e.g., `--background`, `--foreground`).
- When adding new design tokens, define them in `:root` and expose them via Tailwind theme mapping (if used).
- Use semantic tokens, not raw hex values, in components when possible.

## Dark Mode
- Every UI element with color should consider dark mode:
  - text: `text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400`
  - background: `bg-white dark:bg-black`
  - borders: `border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-800`
- Use `transition-colors` for hover/focus color changes.

## Layout Consistency
- Use a consistent container pattern:
  - `max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8`
- If you have a fixed navbar, add top padding to route content:
  - Example: `pt-16` to clear a `h-16` nav.

## Components & Reuse
- Extract repeated Tailwind class patterns into reusable components in `app/components/`.
- Avoid copying large className strings across pages; create a shared component (e.g., `Container`, `Button`, `Section`).

## Accessibility
- Always include visible focus styles:
  - `focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-zinc-400 dark:focus-visible:ring-zinc-600`
- Ensure clickable elements have sufficient hit area:
  - minimum `h-10` and/or `py-2 px-3` for buttons/links.
- Prefer semantic elements (`button`, `nav`, `header`, `main`, `section`) and only add ARIA when needed.

## Class Naming Patterns
- Keep className ordering consistent:
  - Layout (display/position) → Box model (size/spacing) → Typography → Colors → Effects → States
- Use responsive modifiers in ascending order: `sm:` → `md:` → `lg:` → `xl:`.

## Animations & Effects
- Prefer subtle effects:
  - `transition-colors`, `transition-transform`, `duration-200`
- Avoid heavy blur/shadows everywhere; use them intentionally (e.g., navbar backdrop blur).

## Images
- Use `next/image` for images to optimize performance.
- Always set `alt` text.

## Do / Don't Examples

### Do
- `className="text-zinc-600 hover:text-black dark:text-zinc-400 dark:hover:text-white transition-colors"`

### Don't
- Hardcode many hex colors in components
- Duplicate large className strings across multiple files
